-- Wenzhou Businesses Seek Taiwan Bank Investments, Commercial Times Reoprts
-- Weiyi Lim
-- 2010-07-21T23:08:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/wenzhou-businesses-seek-taiwan-bank-investments-commercial-times-reoprts.html

          
          
             Wenzhou companies are seeking
investment in Taiwan banks, the Commercial Times reported,
without saying where it got the information. Wenzhou businessmen
have prepared five billion yuan to take stakes in small-and-
medium banks on the island, according to the paper. Wenzhou
Credit Guarantee Trade led 20 people in a meeting with Ta Chong
Bank Co. chairman last night, the Taipei-based Chinese language
daily said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
